  "text": "The existence of ''pure'' agent-and steward-like behavior is an empirical question. It is possible that in real life such behaviors are mixed and people tend to exhibit features of both at the same time. For example, a manager may believe that organizational interests must be served, but he/she may engage in satisficing [CITATION_1] rather than maximization of the principal's wealth. Satisficing",
